erl) his descriptive psychology, which is concerned with mind as intentionally directed at objects. As Brentano and his students continued in their investigations in descriptive psychology, another side of Austrian phenomenology, namely object theory, became more and more prominent. The philosophical orientation under consideration in this collection of essays is accordingly a two-sided discipline, concerned with both mind and objects, and applicable to various areas of philosophy such as epistemology, philosophy of language, value theory, and ontology.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aPhenomenology. 0aPhilosophy, Austrian. 4aBrentano. 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aHusserl. 4aMeinong. 4aPhilosophie des Geistes. 4aPhilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z978311033122608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z9783110331219oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311032495240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311032548540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110325485423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110325485/original  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-033122-6  eBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012c2002d2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEB